 &HT;    NFC East capsule
 &HT;    By Len Pasquarelli
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON REDSKINS
</P>
<P>
   _ Coach: Norv Turner is 26-37-1 in four seasons with the
Redskins.
</P>
<P>
   _ Last season: 8-7-1, second place in NFC East.
</P>
<P>
   _ Key losses: DT Sean Gilbert (FA), DE Rich Owens (injury), WR
Henry Ellard (retired), OT Ed Simmons (cut), OG Keith Sims (FA), DT
Steve Emtman (cut), DT William Gaines (FA), DT Keith Rucker (cut),
OT Darryl Ashmore (FA).
</P>
<P>
   _ Key gains: DT Dana Stubblefield (FA), DT Dan Wilkinson
(trade), TE Stephen Alexander (D-2), OG Rod Milstead (FA), RB Skip
Hicks (D-3), OG Joe Cocozzo (FA).
</P>
<P>
   _ Outlook: Defense hurt when DE Rich Owens went out for the
season, placing even more emphasis on DTs Stubblefield and
Wilkinson, who cost $16.4 million for 1998. Mike Nolan must improve
run defense, 28th last season. The pressure is on Turner, who
hasn't been to the playoffs, and QB Gus Frerotte. With his job
perhaps on the line, Turner could turn more quickly to backup Jeff
Hostetler if Frerotte struggles. Offensive line has been
overhauled, but the running game is strong.
</P>
<P>
   NEW YORK GIANTS
</P>
<P>
   _ Coach: Jim Fassel is 10-6-1 in one season with the Giants.
</P>
<P>
   _ Last season: 10-5-1, first place in NFC East (lost in first
round of playoffs).
</P>
<P>
   _ Key losses: CB Jason Sehorn (injury), LB Corey Miller
(injury), C Brian Williams (injury), RB Rodney Hampton (cut), DT
Ray Agnew (FA), CB Thomas Randolph (FA), QB Dave Brown (cut), RB
LeShon Johnson (illness).
</P>
<P>
   _ Key gains: FS Shaun Williams (D-1), RB Gary Brown (FA), QB
Kent Graham (FA), WR Joe Jurevicius (D-2), WR Brian Alford (D-3).
</P>
<P>
   _ Outlook: With a playoff collapse in the final two minutes and
the notion that their first division title since 1990 was a fluke,
the Giants enter the season feeling they have much to prove. A
daunting schedule might preclude another 10-victory season, but New
York is better than in '97. The key will be continued progress by
QB Danny Kanell. Look for FB Charles Way to become the featured
rusher and WR Ike Hilliard, who played just two games last year, to
emerge as a top receiver. The defense is outstanding, with no
player over 30.
</P>
<P>
   DALLAS COWBOYS
</P>
<P>
   _ Coach: Chan Gailey is in his first season as an NFL head
coach.
</P>
<P>
