Brown (FA), RB Mario Bates (FA), OT Anthony Clement (D-2b), LB
Patrick Sapp (trade).
</P>
<P>
   _ Outlook: A rare air of expectancy surrounds the Cardinals this
season. Just because they'll be better, however, doesn't make them
a playoff contender. Under vice president Bob Ferguson, the front
office has improved its professionalism and made a big point of
retaining the club's core of good, young players. Quarterback Jake
Plummer gives the franchise a playmaker on the field and a
marketing tool off of it. But holes remain in the offensive line
and secondary.
</P>
<P>
   PHILADELPHIA EAGLES
</P>
<P>
   _ Coach: Ray Rhodes is 27-23-1 in three seasons with the Eagles.
</P>
<P>
   _ Last season: 6-9-1, third place in NFC East.
</P>
<P>
