Keith Sims (FA), OG George Hegamin (FA).
</P>
<P>
   _ Outlook: The Eagles have a new director of football
operations, and they probably will have a new coach, too, by 1999.
Rhodes is a master motivator but also wears on people, and his act
apparently is growing old. The drafts have not provided the nucleus
that ownership wanted, and the Eagles never have run after free
agents. With Watters gone, tiny Charlie Garner, who never has
gained 600 yards in a season, will run the football. QB Bobby
Hoying shows promise but lacks experience.
</P>
