MATT DAMON ZOOMS FROM FROM ZERO TO SEXY 
</HEADLINE>
  1000 words, with color slides and black and white photos of Matt
Damon with Gretchen Mol in a scene from ``Rounders'' and with Robin
Williams in a scene from ``Good Will Hunting.'' 
 By IVOR DAVIS 
 World rights except Great Britain and Australia 
 Distributed by New York Times Special Features)  
<TEXT>
<P>
   Not long ago Matt Damon was counting pennies, living on beans
and wondering if he'd ever get work for bit parts in TV sitcoms.
</P>
<P>
   What a difference a couple of years make.
</P>
<P>
   Today at 28 Damon is the hottest actor in Hollywood. On Sept. 11
he shows up in a leading role in ``Rounders,'' a film about
professional poker players, costarring Edward Norton, Martin
Laundau, John Turturo and John Malkovich. Damon plays a cardsharp
who uses his winnings to put himself through law school.
</P>
