traded for pitcher Randy Johnson, it set the city on fire and put a
good bit of swagger into a team that always has played second- and
third-fiddle to the Braves. Amidst the Houston madness, Johnson
takes the mound against Atlanta tonight. It could offer a glimpse
of what's to come. (Rosenberg, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) ETA 8
p.m. ET.
</P>
