   TEXAS-NUKEDUMP _ WASHINGTON _ The U.S. Senate is expected to
approve an agreement allowing Maine and Vermont to ship nuclear
waste to Texas, despite last-minute lobbying by people who live
near the proposed West Texas dump site. ``I hope we're going to
have some strong opposition (to the waste agreement), but it's an
uphill fight,'' said Sen. Paul Wellstone, D-Minn., the lead
opponent of the agreement in the Senate. (Harlan, Austin
American-Statesman) MOVED.
