<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    We pray for a bad vacation, Mike Kelly
 &HT;    By Gary Nuhn
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   There 'til 9 p.m.''
</P>
<P>
   Nice schedule.
</P>
<P>
   But it's how you win 85 percent of your games. There's only so
much genius in the world, and after that the guy who puts in 15
hours a day has the wall full of plaques.
</P>
<P>
   ``It was 140 degrees,'' Kelly was saying.
</P>
<P>
   He was trying to explain why he lasted less than an hour on the
streets of Nassau on the ship's first stop.
</P>
<P>
   ``The girls went on and had a good time,'' he said. ``They
bought all the trinkets and stuff. I went back and read an
autobiography of Billy Graham. They had a big cooler full of iced
tea and the library was air-conditioned.''
</P>
<P>
   A coach in his element.
</P>
<P>
   He was quite the sight on this cruise. He wore bracelets on both
wrists, plus patches behind both ears, plus he was on a steady diet
of Dramamine because, ``Whenever I'm on water, as soon as I lose
sight port playing cards, trying to figure out what to do with our
four free tickets, and then a bunch of people didn't show up, and
they didn't have to bump anybody.''
</P>
<P>
   Bummer.
</P>
<P>
   And for his daughters, even worse _ Leonardo di Caprio wasn't on
the boat.
</P>
<P>
   Tough world.
</P>
<P>
   Now he's back on the job. It was too hot in Nassau and Key West,
but over the last couple of weeks at Welcome Stadium, where the
temperature on the AstroTurf has reached 136 at times, no big deal.
He could stand out there all day teaching football.
</P>
<P>
   And afterward he goes back to his office and watches films of
the practice. I'm serious. Two cameras sit atop the press box,
taping practice, and when we finished talking at 7 p.m., he was
going back to go watch those tapes.
</P>
<P>
   ``That's absurd,'' I said.
</P>
<P>
   ``I couldn't do without them,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
   UD's season starts Saturday in New Jersey. It's Kelly's next
stop on his way to the Hall of Fame.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
