<P>
   KELSO-COLUMN _ Would somebody please pass the crow? I'd like to
apologize to the multitude of churchgoers I inadvertently
eliminated from existence in my column recently. That's the last
time I'll ever joke around about how you never see a Second Baptist
Church. (Kelso, Austin American-Statesman) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   NETHAWAY-COLUMN _ WACO, Texas _ Out of view of the television
cameras, President Clinton should give charisma lesson to President
Yeltsin. Clinton knows better than anyone that the secret to
maintaining a strong following is charisma, certainly not
character. (Nethaway, Waco Tribune-Herald) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   CERABINO-COLUMN _ Palm Beacher Stephen Fagan wants to set the
record straight. After allegedly kidnapping his two young daughters
from their mother nearly 20 years ago, he didn't take them to live
with a stripper. ``How can one characterize a human being that way
by taking a cheap shot and calling someone a stripper?'' Fagan told
The Palm Beach Daily News in a story published this week. ``She was
an exotic dancer.'' (Fagan, Palm Beach Post) MOVED.
