<P>
   SCIENCE/MEDICINE (a and/or l category)
</P>
<P>
   TEXAS-NUKEDUMP _ WASHINGTON _ The U.S. Senate is expected to
approve an agreement allowing Maine and Vermont to ship nuclear
waste to Texas, despite last-minute lobbying by people who live
near the proposed West Texas dump site. ``I hope we're going to
have some strong opposition (to the waste agreement), but it's an
uphill fight,'' said Sen. Paul Wellstone, D-Minn., the lead
opponent of the agreement in the Senate. (Harlan, Austin
American-Statesman) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   ANTHEM _ One option for Anthem to keep its Medicare HMO in some
less profitable rural and suburban counties is to charge new
monthly premiums to Anthem Senior Advantage members in Montgomery
County. Sources outside the company said Anthem is considering a
proposal that would include monthly premiums of about $40 for
beneficiaries in Montgomery and certain outlying counties, who
currently pay no premiums. (Lamb, Dayton Daily News) MOVED.
</P>
