<P>
   In Miami, Haitians recently gathered at a music store and agreed
to launch a petition drive. In midtown Manhattan, a picket line was
planned outside the Sony Theater on Wednesday evening.
</P>
<P>
   ``We hope to mobilize Haitians in Atlanta to write 20th-Century
Fox, and to do anything else they can to protest,'' Declama said.
</P>
<P>
   She said between 7,000 and 10,000 Haitians live in the Atlanta
area.
</P>
<P>
   A spokeswoman for 20th-Century Fox declined to comment on the
issue Wednesday. A publicist for McMillan said the author also
would not comment.
</P>
<P>
   Meanwhile, Ken Boodhoo, an expert on Haiti at Florida
International University in Boca Raton, Fla., agreed that the
movie's remark was a callous one.
</P>
<P>
   ``Attitudes are stereotypical whether they're white or black,
but it does hurt to know that blacks were involved with this,'' he
said.
</P>
<P>
   ENDIT
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
