husband's arm and sank my nails deep into his flesh. Five times I
bit my lip to muffle my agonized screams, because my children were
watching. I could feel the brand new stitches in my shoulder
straining to hold my severed flesh together. What held the rest of
me together, I do not know. By MONICA FRAZIER ANDERSON. Story will
