   BASEBALL-WEDDING &QL;
</P>
<P>
   FORT WORTH, Texas _ The Reds and the Blues would probably prefer
that this story run on the sports page. Especially the Reds. After
all, this was a baseball game. Last Saturday, 19 guys withstood the
heat to replay history, a time a few years back when many of them
pitched, caught, slammed, stole and ran for the Southwest High
School Raiders. Most of them, still in great shape, meant business,
even if there were other motives for calling this game. The reunion
was in celebration of 24-year-old Monte Pearson, who today will wed
his high-school sweetheart, Jodi Sturgiss, at First United
Methodist Church in downtown Fort Worth. By MARK LOWRY. Story will
move in ``l'' lifestyle category. &QL; 
