<P>
   But he can't. This is the common thread that connects every time
I've seen Guadarrama playing saxophone, whether he was with the
Fort Worth Guitar Army at Billy Bob's last November or Latin
Express at the J&AMP;J Blues Bar a couple weeks ago: He shows up, plays
some great sax, and then is gone, into the night, back to his
9-to-5 gig, which in his case is a midnight-to-noon gig, fixing
laser printers for Xerox, where he has worked for 19 years. By DAVE
FERMAN. Story will move in ``e'' entertainment category. &QL; 
