<DOCNO> NYT19980902.0193 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-02 15:30 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A5226 &Cx1f; ttx-z
r d &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-HOTDOGS-1600(2ndTake)     09-02 0479
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-HOTDOGS-1600(2ndTake)-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
FRANK TALK, JUST IN TIME FOR YOUR LABOR DAY COOKOUT
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   UNDATED _ is the worst. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   A CONEY ISLAND
</P>
<P>
   SERVES 10-12
</P>
<P>
   1-pound package cooked hot dogs
</P>
<P>
   1 package hot dog buns
</P>
<P>
   Mustard
</P>
<P>
   Chili without beans, recipe follows
</P>
<P>
   5 medium raw onions, chopped
</P>
<P>
   Serve hot dogs on buns with a swab of mustard, some chili and a
hearty sprinkling of onions.
</P>
<P>
   Chili:
</P>
<P>
   6 tablespoons butter, margarine or vegetable oil
</P>
<P>
   6 medium onions, sliced
</P>
<P>
   1 1/2 pounds ground beef
</P>
<P>
   3 20-ounce cans tomatoes
</P>
<P>
   6-ounce can tomato paste
</P>
<P>
   1 cup beer
</P>
<P>
   1 tablespoon salt
</P>
<P>
   1/2 teaspoon Tabasco
</P>
<P>
   2-4 tablespoons chili powder
</P>
<P>
   2 12-ounce cans whole-kernel corn
</P>
<P>
   Melt butter, margarine or oil in large saucepan. Add onion and
cook until tender but not brown. Add ground beef and cook until
lightly browned, breaking up with a fork. Add tomatoes, tomato
paste, beer, salt, Tabasco and chili powder. Cover and simmer 45
minutes. Add corn and simmer 15 minutes longer.
</P>
<P>
   Nutritional analysis per serving: 521 calories, 24 grams fat, 55
grams carbohydrates, 24 grams protein, 60 milligrams cholesterol,
1,643 milligrams sodium, 42 percent of calories from fat.
</P>
<P>
   PAT AND MIKE'S BICKERSON SPECIAL
</P>
<P>
   Serves 6
</P>
<P>
   6 pieces white sandwich bread, toasted and buttered
</P>
<P>
   4 or 5 hot dogs, sliced
</P>
<P>
   2 tomatoes, sliced thin
</P>
<P>
   6 slices Cheddar cheese
</P>
<P>
   Worcestershire sauce, to taste
</P>
<P>
   On toast, place slices of cooked hot dogs. Top with thin slices
of tomato and slices of cheese.
</P>
<P>
   Place under broiler until hot and bubbly. Top with dash or two
of Worcestershire sauce.
</P>
<P>
   Nutritional analysis per serving: 323 calories, 18 grams fat, 27
grams carbohydrates, 15 grams protein, 52 milligrams cholesterol,
709 milligrams sodium, 49 percent of calories from fat.
</P>
<P>
   SOUTH OF THE BORDER FRANCOS
</P>
<P>
   Serves 16
</P>
<P>
   2 pounds of hot dogs
</P>
<P>
   16 tortillas
</P>
<P>
   16-ounce can refried beans, heated
</P>
<P>
   1 cup shredded Cheddar cheese
</P>
<P>
   Sliced scallions
</P>
<P>
   Grill franks for about 10 minutes, or until bubbly hot.
</P>
<P>
   While franks cook, heat tortillas on grill, turning with tongs.
</P>
<P>
   Place franks in tortillas and top with beans, cheese and
scallions. Roll up and serve.
</P>
<P>
   Nutritional analysis per serving: 312 calories, 14 grams fat, 35
grams carbohydrates, 13 grams protein, 33 milligrams cholesterol,
719 milligrams sodium, 39 percent of calories from fat.
</P>
<P>
   _ ``The Hot Dog Cookbook,'' by Jess M. Brallier (Globe Pequot,
$9.95)
</P>
<P>
   (Beverly Bundy is food editor for the Fort Worth Star-Telegram.
Send recipes and requests to Beverly Bundy, Fort Worth
Star-Telegram, Box 1870, Fort Worth, Texas 76101. Or E-mail to
bbundy(at)star-telegram.com. Include a daytime phone number.
Responses to requests will be made only through this column. Visit
the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide Web:
www.star-telegram.com)
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
