<P>
   BOX-EVANDER _ Like many other Atlantans, Evander Holyfield is
working at home these days. He gets up before dawn to train in his
personal gym for the Sept. 19 bout against Vaughn Bean at the
Georgia Dome, and squeezes in the occasional parental duty between
workouts at his estate in Fairburn. He and personal trainer Tim
Hallmark are bunking in the unfinished but livable mansion while
Holyfield's wife and children stay in the existing home. (Schultz,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution) ETA 8 p.m. ET. WITH PHOTOS.
