<P>
   RUSSIA-SUMMIT (Moscow) _ President Clinton signaled Wednesday
that the West would be willing to expand its program of financial
assistance if Russia carried out tough economic reforms. Clinton's
message was intended to encourage the Yeltsin government to stick
with its pro-capitalist course despite the nation's deepening
economic crisis. By Michael R. Gordon.
</P>
