marketing of a drug, tamoxifen, to reduce women's' risk of
developing breast cancer. According to the National Cancer
Institute, tamoxifen is the first drug that can diminish the
chances that healthy people would get a major cancer. But the drug
is not a panacea, experts warn. By Gina Kolata.
