<HEADLINE>
OUT-OF-THE-ORDINARY GRILLED PIZZA TOPPINGS 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 BY JUDY WALKER AND PENELOPE CORCORAN  
 c.1998 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   UNDATED - Instead of heavy sauces or lots of cheese, keep
toppings light and fresh for grilled pizzas, says Chris Bianco of
Pizzeria Bianco in Phoenix. Think of it as a flatbread with
toppings.
</P>
<P>
   Just olive oil, rosemary and salt on a piece of grilled pizza
dough makes a wonderful appetizer. Or you can add two or three
tablespoons of chopped fresh herbs or two or three teaspoons of
dried herbs to pizza dough before cooking. You also can add roasted
garlic to the dough.
</P>
<P>
   Here are some pizza toppings you won't find on a big chain's
delivery menu:
</P>
<P>
   Grilled delights
</P>
<P>
   - Chicken, cut into bite-size pieces.
</P>
<P>
   - Red bell peppers, roasted, peeled, cut into strips or bits.
</P>
<P>
   - Shrimp basted with olive oil and maybe a little lime juice.
</P>
<P>
   - Roasted green chiles (peeled, seeded, cut into strips).
</P>
<P>
   - Pineapple slices.
</P>
<P>
   - Japanese eggplant.
</P>
<P>
   - Portobellos (sliced). &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
Get ready ahead of time
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
- Crumbled and cooked mild or hot Italian sausage, removed from
casing before cooking, well-drained.
</P>
<P>
   - Oil-cured or kalamata olives or any favorite olive, sliced off
the pit.
</P>
<P>
   - Roasted garlic.
</P>
<P>
   - Sun-dried tomatoes in oil, drained, chopped.
</P>
<P>
   - Crumbles of goat cheese or Gorgonzola.
</P>
<P>
   - Thin slices of smoked cheeses such as Gouda. &QL; 
 &QL; 
Our favorite combos
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   - BLT Pizza: Slices of tomato and chopped crisp bacon topped
with a pile of chilled shredded iceberg (lightly tossed with mayo
and black pepper).
</P>
<P>
   - Drained, sliced fresh mozzarella, thin slices of tomato,
shredded fresh basil.
</P>
<P>
   - Smoked salmon (lox style), capers, goat cheese.
</P>
<P>
   - Thinly sliced pears and Maytag blue cheese.
</P>
<P>
   - Thinly sliced apples and Brie.
</P>
<P>
   - Spinach and goat cheese.
</P>
<P>
   - Feta, cooked chicken, kalamata olives.
</P>
<P>
   - Sauteed mushrooms and fresh Parmesan.
</P>
<P>
   - Artichoke hearts, feta, cooked chicken.
</P>
<P>
   - Prosciutto shreds and grilled pineapple.
</P>
<P>
   - Roasted garlic and three or four different types of cheeses.
</P>
<P>
   - Peanut butter and jelly (really!). &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
