BRITS-BOWL (Los Angeles) _ British actors Lynn Redgrave and Patrick
Stewart got hooked on American musicals and theater at an early
age, and they'll exhibit their hubris this weekend at the Hollywood
Bowl, as part of a musical bill that Redgrave jokingly dubs ``Brits
On Broadway.'' By Reed Johnson. 
. 
The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following stories
today for use by NYTimes News Service clients. They will move in
the ``l'' lifestyle news file. For questions, contact Jimmy Johnson
at the Daily News, (818) 713-3695. 
. 
GALA-FASHION (Los Angeles) _ Don't count on your little black dress
as a catch-all for the upcoming black-tie season, which begins next
week with the L.A. Opera's opening night of ``Carmen.'' Standards
and theme parties are back in style and you'll be seeing
invitations to wear something from the roaring '20s, the swing
dance era, or the cocktail-crazed '50s. By Barbara De Witt. 
. 

