   SUDAN-BOMBING (Washington) _ Sudan's ambassador to the United
States on Wednesday accused Washington of ``a Wild West,
shoot-first-boys and ask-questions-later philosophy'' in the attack
on a pharmaceutical plant suspected of being a secret
chemical-weapons facility in his capital, Khartoum. By Tim Weiner.
