MONTINI-COLUMN (Phoenix) - Were it not for the time-consuming and
costly efforts of Phoenix City Council, the good citizens of our
community would have no concept of the important work performed for
us by people like ``Jesse.'' I didn't realize it myself until
shortly after noon Wednesday, when the young, thin woman took her
first slow steps onto the stage of The Jungle Cabaret downtown. By
E.J.MONTINI. Story will move in the ``A'' and ``K'' categories.
