<P>
   MURRAY-CLINTON (Washington) Washington Sen. Patty Murray
Wednesday said she is angry and hurt by President Clinton's
conduct, and that she does not believe he adequately understands
how painful his behavior has been to his supporters. Murray's
comments, during a briefing for reporters, were her most extensive
to date on the Clinton-Lewinsky matter, and come as Wash. Rep.
Linda Smith is attacking Murray for failing to hold Clinton to the
same standard to which she held Brock Adams and Bob Packwood.
Murray's remarks are still less pointed than those of Richard
Gephardt or Dianne Feinstein, but given her predilection for mild
rhetoric, this is as far as she's going.
</P>
<P>
   By Michael Paulson. (story will move in the ``w'' category)
</P>
<P>
   BOEING-AIRSHOW (Undated) One of the world's biggest airshows
kicks off Monday outside of London, with Airbus strutting in on the
heels of recent headline-grabbing victories over Boeing, and the
Seattle-based aerospace giant reeling from a top management shakeup
and one of its worst years ever. Among the key orders Boeing may
announce at the airshow are for its new 100-passenger 717, which is
supposed to fly for the first time today from Long Beach.
</P>
