<HEADLINE>
UNCLE SAM BRINGS YOU THE PERFECT WOMAN
</HEADLINE>
  
 (Eds: This story also moved in the ``a'' national news file)  
 By LEAH GARCHIK  
 c.1998 San Francisco Chronicle
<TEXT>
<P>
   There's already one offspring, a grown man, but another, an
adult woman, is on the way. Officials of the National Highway
Traffic Safety Administration recently completed drafting standards
for Hybrid II Female, the feds' first made-to-order female crash
dummy.
</P>
<P>
   This lovely lady, says the Wall Street Journal, is 5 feet tall,
weighs 108 pounds, contains 80 electronic sensors and will cost
about $100,000.
</P>
<P>
   She is bald (because hair would complicate measurements of head
impact) and mainly free of curves. Her skin is shiny and plastic,
and her clothing, according to federal standards, looks like pink
long underwear.
</P>
<P>
   Meanwhile, &UR; Jason Alexander &LR; 's celebration of the demise of
``shoulder pad falsies'' has been ruined by a glance downward:
``Women have gone from looking like Green Bay Packer linebackers to
looking like Budweiser Clydesdales.''
</P>
<P>
   In keeping with this theme (the quest for perfection, if you
forgot), the St. Francis Hotel in San Francisco has proudly
announced that it will be the site of the Playboy 2000 Playmate
Search from September 7 to 9.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; FLASH &LR;
</P>
<P>
   _ Among the guest celebrities who accepted Microsoft co-founder
 &UR; Paul Allen &LR; 's invitation to join more than 500 well-wishers for a
four-day luxury Alaska cruise honoring  &UR; Bill &LR; 
 &UR; Gates  &LR; were  &UR; Candice Bergen &LR; ,  &UR; James Cameron  &LR; and  &UR; Dan Aykroyd &LR; .
</P>
<P>
   _ Floating financial forecast? Despite the stock market's
recovery on Tuesday,  &UR; P.W. &LR;  noticed that one of the ships that
arrived from Asia at the Port of Oakland was the  &UR; President &LR; 
 &UR; Hoover &LR; .
</P>
<P>
   _  &UR; Oprah Winfrey &LR;  will get naked, says the BBC, in a love scene
with  &UR; Danny Glover  &LR; in the forthcoming movie ``Beloved,'' which is
based on  &UR; Toni Morrison &LR; 's novel.
</P>
<P>
   _  &UR; Madonna &LR;  has joined a group of mothers waging a legal fight
against the construction of a 41-story YMCA residential tower on
her block on the Upper West Side of Manhattan. An affidavit she
signed stated that in light of the recent scaffolding accident in
Times Square, the proposed construction poses a ``hazard for me and
my child.''
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; WOMEN PAY THEMSELVES LESS &LR;
</P>
<P>
   Women tend to value the work they do 18 percent less than men
value the same work, according to a study done at the Stanford
Graduate School of Business.
</P>
<P>
   Assistant Professor  &UR; John Jost  &LR; asked a group of women and a
group of men _ all of them undergraduates at Yale University _ to
write an essay about shopping for computers. When the essays were
complete, every one of the 132 students was asked how much they
would pay someone who had written such an essay.
</P>
<P>
   As a group, the women paid themselves 18 percent less than the
men did. The papers themselves, judged by an independent panel,
were found to be equal when judged by gender.
</P>
<P>
   Jost said he was disturbed at the huge gap in the figures, even
in an Ivy League school where feminism is generally popular.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; INVITATION TO THE CATHEDRAL &LR;
</P>
<P>
   At a Mass in St. Patrick's Cathedral last Sunday, Monsignor
 &UR; Anthony Della Villa &LR;  announced that members of a Jewish
congregation had been invited to use the church for the High
Holidays, reports the New York Post.
</P>
<P>
   New York's Central Synagogue had been burned in a fire the week
before, and the monsignor said that the invitation had come from
Cardinal &UR; John O'Connor &LR; .
</P>
<P>
   ( &UR; Elvis Presley &LR;  fans who gathered in Israel to commemorate his
birthday a few weeks ago believe that the King was Jewish. ``Elvis
and Gladys,'' a 1985 book by  &UR; Elaine Dundy &LR; , claims that Elvis'
maternal great-great-grandmother,  &UR; Nancy Tackett &LR; , was Jewish.
</P>
<P>
   According to Jewish law, that means Elvis was Jewish. ``It was
something Elvis was aware of,''  &UR; Todd Morgan &LR;  of Graceland told the
Wall Street Journal, ``and certainly was sensitive to.'')
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; WHO SAID WHAT &LR;
</P>
<P>
   ``Everyone looks at me like I'm a leper above the eyes.''
</P>
<P>
   _ Drew Barrymore on her overplucked eyebrows, which Premiere
magazine calls ``endearing.''
</P>
