<SLUG> BC-HEROIN-RECOVERING-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
TREATMENT PROGRAM GIVES ADDICT HOPE FOR TOMORROW
</HEADLINE>
 
EDS; One of 22 articles (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By DOMINGO RAMIREZ JR. 
c.1998 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   FORT WORTH, Texas _ In the next month, Christopher Cook plans to
get a job, open a savings account, find a place to live and buy a
vehicle.
</P>
<P>
   If his goals appear ambitious, the 24-year-old already has
achieved a more formidable objective: completing 20 months in
residential drug treatment for his heroin addiction. He is almost
ready to move into the next phase of the treatment program at
Cenikor Foundation.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm a little nervous,'' Cook said. ``I wonder how it'll be on
my own.''
</P>
<P>
   Cook began using heroin at 18, and at one time he had a
$200-per-day addiction. He sold marijuana, LSD and heroin to pay
for his habit.
</P>
<P>
   To get more money, Cook stole building materials from
construction sites, reselling them to hardware stores. He took
electronic equipment and jewelry from his family.
</P>
<P>
   Cook was arrested so many times that he can't remember the exact
number. But his last jail stay in 1996 persuaded him to seek help.
He checked into Cenikor in January 1997.
</P>
<P>
   ``When I first met him, he was a very irresponsible person who
let everything bother him,'' said Harold Fair, Cook's counselor at
Cenikor. ``This was someone who couldn't even get up in the morning
on time.
</P>
<P>
   ``Then one day, it was like a light came on in his head. He
changed, and he's never looked back.''
</P>
<P>
   Cook said it wasn't easy.
</P>
<P>
   ``The majority of people who I've seen come here don't finish,''
he said. ``It's highly structured and you have to be ready for
it.''
</P>
<P>
   For most of the past 20 months, Cook has been on a three-member
landscaping crew that leaves the Fort Worth facility at sunup and
returns at sundown.
</P>
<P>
   ``Right now, it doesn't seem like I've been here that long,''
Cook said. ``It was rough at first, but I know even after I leave
that I'll remember where I came from.''
</P>
<P>
   (Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide
Web: www.star-telegram.com) &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
