<TEXT>
<P>
   &UR;  &QL;  &LR; 
 &UR;  &QL;  &LR; 
 &UR; CKS  &LR; _ In a merger of Bay Area Internet-consulting pioneers, design
firm USWeb Corp. yesterday agreed to buy advertising agency CKS
Group Inc. in a stock swap worth about $300 million.
</P>
<P>
   The combined company will resurface under the new name Reinvent
Communications Inc., which company officials hope will take
advantage of the two firm's strengths _ USWeb's technological
acumen and CKS's creative marketing prowess. By Benny Evangelista
</P>
<P>
   &UR; HOMEPAGE  &LR; _ Forget push technology. Forget portals. Forget
e-commerce.
</P>
<P>
   The hottest things on the Internet _ this week at least _ are
community home pages.
</P>
<P>
   These virtual neighborhoods are a cross between chat rooms,
where strangers message each other online _ and personal home
pages, those Web sites that let people show off themselves, their
pets and their hobbies. By Jon Swartz
</P>
<P>
   &UR; DIGITAL  &LR; _ Tom Abate's technology column.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; PEOPLE IN TECH: &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; YU  &LR; _ Intel's rise to the ranks of a superpower in the
semiconductor industry has been due in part to a willingness to
take risks.
</P>
<P>
   As a senior vice president and the man in charge of Intel's
microprocessors, Albert Yu details some of those risks in his new
book, ``Creating the Digital Future.''
</P>
<P>
   But Yu's book leaves out the one story that illustrates his own
risk-taking credentials. By Dan Fost
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
