<HEADLINE>
ADDICT TAKES ONE STEP FORWARD, TWO STEPS BACK
</HEADLINE>
 
EDS: One of 22 stories (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By CAROL LEWIS 
c.1998 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Jennifer Kogge, a 23-year-old Colleyville woman who was in
treatment for heroin addiction at a California recovery center, has
relapsed twice since the Star-Telegram wrote about her in April,
her father says.
</P>
<P>
   But she has been clean the past 60 days, working in a French
restaurant and living at Safe Harbor House in Costa Mesa, Calif.
</P>
<P>
   Chuck Kogge, who visited his daughter this month at the recovery
home for women, said he has learned to take her recovery one day at
a time.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's a continuous struggle,'' he said. ``To them, relapsing is
like smoking another cigarette; it's no big deal.
</P>
<P>
   ``We know it's the possibility of death.''
</P>
<P>
   Jennifer Kogge has been battling heroin addiction for more than
five years. She overdosed on the drug in October 1996 and began
injecting it into her veins within two weeks.
</P>
<P>
   Before entering treatment last year, she was living on the
streets, surviving on Snickers candy bars and the heroin she pumped
through the veins in her bony arms. She had lost 45 of her 120
pounds. Her parents were convinced that she was a heartbeat from
death.
</P>
<P>
   Safe Harbor House is not as structured as the first private
California center that Kogge was in. Daily Alcoholics Anonymous and
Narcotics Anonymous meetings, and the other women at the house,
provide support.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's not a lock-down structure,'' said William Mangan, the
house's co-owner. ``It's halfway between being in treatment and
being on your own. It gets them acclimated to society.''
</P>
<P>
   Although his daughter is in recovery, Chuck Kogge does not
believe that the battle is won.
</P>
<P>
   ``When she relapses, it is scary. It makes me feel sick,'' he
said. ``It's very tough to divorce yourself completely.''
</P>
<P>
   (Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide
Web: www.star-telegram.com) &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
