<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    SEC Notes
 &HT;    By Tony Barnhart and Wendy Parker
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ALABAMA vs. BYU, Saturday, 7 p.m., ESPN
</P>
<P>
   Cornerback Fernando Bryant said there is ``no way'' he will miss
Saturday's opener with BYU despite a sprained knee suffered last
week. Bryant, who is also slated to play wide receiver, sprained
his knee while returning a kickoff. Bryant's injury is the third to
a defensive back as Antoine Hunter sprained an ankle and Kecalf
Bailey had to leave practice with severe cramps. ... Sophomore
linebacker Travis Carroll is still considered questionable for BYU
after getting hit with a helmet underneath his left shoulder pad on
Aug. 20. Senior Tito Smith would start in his place. ... Ryan
Flugner, a 5-10 junior, has won the placekicking job over sophomore
A.J. Diaz. Diaz will still be used on kickoffs.
</P>
<P>
   ARKANSAS vs. SW Louisiana, Saturday, 7 p.m.
</P>
<P>
   The return of running back Madre Hill should make Razorbacks
fans happy. Hill, who has missed the last two seasons recovering
from a knee injury, will get a majority of the load at tailback
right from the start. ``The doctors have said he's ready to go, so
we're going to turn him loose,'' first-year head coach Houston Nutt
said.... Although Nutt and most of his staff are new, only three
new starters are projected to break into the lineup: defensive end
Carlos Hall, cornerbacks Orlando Green and Ontraia Moss and
flankers Michael Williams, Michael Snowden or Emanuel Smith.
...Arkansas men's athletics director Frank Broyles unveiled plans
this week for a $50 million expansion of Razorback Stadium. The
project would add roughly 17,000 seats and luxury boxes to push
capacity close to 70,000.
</P>
<P>
   AUBURN vs. Virginia, today, 8 p.m., ESPN
</P>
<P>
   Karl Levine will start at center and Cordele's Meiko Collier
will be the backup quarterback for tonight's game with Virginia.
Levine, a 6-3, 279-pound senior from Fort Walton Beach, Fla., moved
into the spot when junior T.J. Dunnigan quit the team in August.
Collier, a 6-2, 231-pound freshman, sat out last season as a
redshirt. ... Auburn has won 20 straight regular-season
non-conference games dating to 1991. ... This will be the first
time Auburn has opened at home against a ranked opponent. Virginia
is No. 16. ... Markeith Cooper, a 5-7, 165-pound running back, has
been moved to wide receiver and will start tonight.
</P>
<P>
   FLORIDA vs. The Citadel, Saturday, 6 p.m.
</P>
<P>
   Quarterback Doug Johnson finally started throwing without pain
this week but will still not play in Saturday's opener. Sophomore
Jesse Palmer was named the starter over a week ago. ``In a week or
two I'll be at full strength,'' said Johnson. ... Coach Steve
Spurrier said Palmer would play well into the second half
``regardless of what the score is.'' Walk-on Larry Richart will be
the first quarterback off the bench, followed by redshirt freshman
Tim Olmstead. ... Spurrier said as many as seven true freshmen will
see action on Saturday, which would match the most the Gators have
used since 1990. ... Offensive tackle Cooper Carlisle (shoulder)
and tailback Earnest Graham (shoulder) are questionable for the
game.
</P>
<P>
   KENTUCKY at Louisville, Saturday,
</P>
<P>
   3 p.m., Fox SS
</P>
<P>
   The Wildcats' youth on defense has allowed nine true freshmen to
make the two-deep roster, with defensive end Dennis Johnson and
defensive back Anthony Wajda expected to crack the starting unit,
coach Hal Mumme said. Seven starters on defense will be starting
their first collegiate games. ... Returning starting safety Willie
Gary, one of the leaders on defense, is listed as questionable with
a sprained ankle....Saturday's game will be the first for the
Wildcats in Louisville since 1915, and will be the first of several
in the next few years. Earlier this week, Kentucky renewed its
series with the Cardinals for another six years to the year 2005.
The two schools hadn't played each other in 70 years until resuming
the rivalry in 1994.
</P>
<P>
   LSU vs. Arkansas State, Sept. 12
</P>
<P>
   LSU's backfield may be taking another hit. A month ago, All-SEC
candidate Cecil Collins was kicked off the team after a brush with
the law. Now it appears that Rondell Mealey will miss next
Saturday's opening game with Arkansas State. Mealey, the backup to
All-SEC tailback Kevin Faulk, has not been able to get over a foot
injury suffered last spring. He has gotten virtually no work in
preseason drills. Coach Gerry DiNardo indicated this week that he
was not sure when Mealey would return. ``My experience is that if a
guy's not progressing, he's not progressing,'' he said. With Mealey
out, more of the work load will be on Faulk, senior Kendall
Cleveland and redshirt freshman LaVar Johnson. ... Craig Nall has
been named No. 2 quarterback behind starter Herb Tyler.
</P>
<P>
   MISSISSIPPI vs. Memphis, Saturday,
</P>
<P>
   12:30 p.m., WATL
</P>
<P>
   The opener against Memphis will mark the first game in expanded
Vaught-Hemingway Stadium. All 50,577 seats _ including about 8,000
new ones _ will be available for the game. Coach Tommy Tuberville
is ``disappointed with ticket sales,'' adding that more than 7,000
tickets were still available. And that figure assumes that Memphis
sells its entire allotment and all Ole Miss student tickets are
claimed for the Labor Day holiday weekend game. Ole Miss and
Memphis _ located about 75 miles apart _ are renewing a series that
took a two-year hiatus after being contested all but four years
between 1949-95.
</P>
<P>
   MISSISSIPPI STATE vs. Vanderbilt, Saturday,
</P>
<P>
   6 p.m., ESPN2
</P>
<P>
   Coach Jackie Sherrill said this week that he will play the four
players arrested on battery charges last week. Starting center
Craig Moore, starting split end Kevin Cooper, backup split end
Lahitia Grant and backup right cornerback Kenzaki Jones were
released by university authorities, but Sherrill said he will not
determine their future playing status until he looks into the
matter personally....Matt Wyatt's job as the No. 1 quarterback is
secure, but Sherrill plans to take a look at backups Rod Morgan and
Wayne Madkin against Vandy. Wyatt, with 2,199 passing yards, needs
224 more to move into ninth place in school history....About a
dozen Bulldog freshmen also are expected to get some playing time
in the opener.
</P>
<P>
   SOUTH CAROLINA vs. Ball State, Saturday, 7 p.m.
</P>
<P>
   Reserve safety Maurice Henderson has been suspended for
Saturday's game after violating an unspecified team rule. ... Coach
Brad Scott said Wednesday that quarterback Anthony Wright is 100
percent after suffering a severe knee injury in the ninth game of
the 1997 season. ``When the surgery first took place there was a
question if he could ever return to football,'' said Scott. ``He's
far exceeded everyone's expectations with his comeback. The way
he's throwing and running, you wouldn't believe he was hurt so
bad.''... South Carolina has won three straight home openers. ...
This is the first time an SEC team has played Ball State.
</P>
<P>
   TENNESSEE at Syracuse, Saturday,
</P>
<P>
   noon, ESPN
</P>
<P>
   Besides new quarterback Tee Martin, the Volunteer with the most
to prove on Saturday will be sophomore punter David Leaverton.
Leaverton, a high school star from Texas, won the punting job at
the beginning of last season. But in the second game against UCLA,
Leaverton gave up a safety when he missed a snap while trying to
call time out. Then he shanked the free kick. His next two punts
went 17 and 25 yards. UT overcame all that to win 30-24 but
Leaverton went to the sidelines for the rest of the season. He
thought about quitting the team but was talked out of it by his
parents. ``He has just got a lot of ability. But until he gets in a
game and actually does it, we won't know for sure,'' said head
coach Phillip Fulmer.
</P>
<P>
   VANDERBILT at Mississippi State, Saturday,
</P>
<P>
   6 p.m., ESPN2
</P>
<P>
   Former running back Jimmy Williams isn't the only skilled
offensive player moved to the other side of the ball. Vandy has
converted Jamail Carter, last year's backup quarterback, to strong
safety, where he will play behind Ainsley Battles but is expected
to get considerable playing time. Williams, who is replacing
All-SEC cornerback Corey Chavous, has made the adjustment well,
according to coach Woody Widenhofer....The leader of the secondary,
cornerback Fred Vinson, has been rated the best cover corner man in
the nation by The Sporting News. ... Junior Hi Lewis is still
listed as the starter at quarterback, a position in which Vandy has
no players with college experience.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
