<SLUG> BC-FBC-USC-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
USC'S CLAIBORNE PUT HIS WEIGHT INTO GAME
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By SCOTT WOLF  
 c.1998 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ USC linebacker Chris Claiborne weighed himself
this week and discovered he was five pounds lighter, thanks to
going 83 out of a possible 87 plays against Purdue.
</P>
<P>
   But Claiborne wouldn't have it any other way, even if it were
118 degrees at the Coliseum.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's fun,'' Claiborne said. ``It didn't hit me until after the
game. I just went home and rested and my mom kept giving me a lot
of water.''
</P>
<P>
   Claiborne probably had the best performance of any USC player,
with nine tackles and an interception. He also distinguished
himself with his leadership, keeping calm early despite the fact
Purdue controlled the ball for 13 of the game's first 15 minutes.
</P>
<P>
   ``I've got to be honest. I thought, `Oh no, not again (this
season),''' Claiborne said. ``But I decided I've got to stay cool
and keep it to myself. I can't complain. I've got to set an
example.''
</P>
<P>
   The weight loss didn't bother him, even though he dropped to 245
pounds.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'll be a lot faster,'' Claiborne said.
</P>
<P>
   Coming back: Linebacker Mark Cusano (hamstring) continues to
work his way back slowly, after being limited to 27 plays against
Purdue. As of today, Zeke Moreno remains the starter.
</P>
<P>
   ``That's going to be a battle,'' USC coach Paul Hackett said.
``When Mark's at the top of his game, I would expect he'll be at
the top at that position.''
</P>
<P>
   Pearsall hurting: Strong safety Grant Pearsall said he's
questionable for the San Diego State game and is not going to rush
his return, after straining a ligament in his right knee. ``I came
back a little too soon,'' Pearsall said. ``I don't want to throw
away the whole year.''
</P>
<P>
   Quarterbacks, quarterbacks: Freshman Carson Palmer continued to
get equal time at quarterback, although Hackett says he will
eventually give Mike Van Raaphorst 60 percent of the snaps.
</P>
<P>
   Once again, Wednesday, Palmer continued to be impressive with
several long pass completions.
</P>
<P>
   Hackett said if Jason Thomas undergoes ankle surgery, he will
use Quincy Woods as the No.3 quarterback.
</P>
<P>
   Rendon still suspended: Reserve kicker Adam Rendon had a meeting
with Hackett but remains indefinitely suspended.
</P>
<P>
   ``It doesn't look good,'' Hackett said. ``(But) I'm not saying
that the door is totally closed.''
</P>
<P>
   Hackett refused to provide an explanation of what Rendon would
have to do to get back on the team. Rendon had been originally
suspended for missing classes and study hall sessions.
</P>
<P>
   First-game jitters: The players weren't the only ones nervous
against Purdue. ``We had some plays I called wrong,'' Hackett said.
``I called two plays right out of the (Kansas City) Chiefs'
playbook.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
